overview of Tetra
The Terrestrial Trunked Radio (TETRA) protocol is a digital trunked mobile radio standard developed to meet the needs of professional mobile radio users, particularly in the public safety and security sectors. It is widely used in Europe and other parts of the world for mission-critical communications.

